A. Increasing the number of replication workers requires an increase in batch size in a
farmed environment.
B. Increasing the number of replication workers increases the number of connections to the
IBM FileNet Image Services server.
C. Increasing the number of replication workers increases the Java virtual machine (JVM)
memory that is used on the application server.
D. Monitoring the system vitals such as CPU, memory and throughput rates is essential. As
system resources are maxed out, increasing thenumber of workers does not increase
performance and may decrease performance.
